        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- When does it activate -->
      <section id="activation" style="margin-bottom:3rem;padding-top:2rem;border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <h2 class="section-h2">When does the maturity number activate?</h2>

        <p style="color:var(--color-body-text);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">
          The standard answer is somewhere between 35 and 40. But it's not like flipping a switch. You don't wake up on your 36th birthday with a new personality. It's more like a gradient. The energy fades in over several years.
        </p>

        <p style="color:var(--color-body-text);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">
          Some people notice it earlier, especially if they've gone through major life events that forced growth. Divorce, career collapse, loss, relocation. These things can accelerate the maturity number's arrival because they strip away the surface-level identity and expose what's underneath.
        </p>

        <p style="color:var(--color-body-text);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">
          Others feel it later, closer to their mid-forties. The timing depends on how much inner work you've done and how much life has asked of you. But almost everyone reports the same general experience: a shift in priorities. Things that used to matter intensely start to feel less urgent. And things you never paid attention to suddenly feel important.
        </p>

        <p style="color:var(--color-body-text);line-height:1.8;">
          What that means is simple: if you're under 35, your maturity number is a preview. It shows you where you're headed. If you're over 40, look back at the last few years. You'll probably recognize the shift. And if you're right in that 35–40 window? Pay attention. The transition is happening now.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <section id="faq" style="margin-bottom:3rem;padding-top:2rem;border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <h2 class="section-h2" style="text-align:center;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details>
            <summary>
              What is a maturity number in numerology?
              <svg class="faq-chevron" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Your maturity number is calculated by adding your Life Path Number and your Expression Number, then reducing to a single digit (or master number). It represents the energy that grows strongest in the second half of your life, typically after age 35–40. Think of it as the person you're becoming after enough life experience has merged your innate gifts with your natural direction.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>
              How do I calculate my maturity number?
              <svg class="faq-chevron" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Add your Life Path Number to your Expression Number, then reduce the result to a single digit. For example: if your life path is 7 and your expression number is 5, that's 7 + 5 = 12, then 1 + 2 = 3. Your maturity number is 3. If the sum is 11, 22, or 33, don't reduce further. Those are master numbers.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>
              When does the maturity number take effect?
              <svg class="faq-chevron" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">The maturity number typically activates between ages 35 and 40. Some people feel it earlier, some later, but that mid-life window is when most people notice the shift. It doesn't arrive all at once. It's more like a slow fade-in. You start feeling drawn toward things you never cared about before, or priorities that seemed foreign begin to make sense.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>
              Is the maturity number the same as the life path number?
              <svg class="faq-chevron" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">No. Your life path number comes from your birth date alone and represents your core energy from birth. Your maturity number combines your life path with your expression number (from your full birth name) and represents who you're growing into. They can be the same number by coincidence, but they're calculated differently and mean different things.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>
              Can you have a master number as your maturity number?
              <svg class="faq-chevron" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Yes. If your Life Path Number plus your Expression Number adds up to 11, 22, or 33, you have a master maturity number. Don't reduce it further. A master maturity number means the second half of your life carries amplified spiritual energy, higher intensity, bigger purpose, and often a stronger pull toward service or large-scale impact.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>
              What if my maturity number is the same as my life path number?
              <svg class="faq-chevron" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">When your maturity number matches your life path, it doubles down on that energy. The second half of life intensifies what was already there from the start. You don't shift direction. You go deeper. A life path 7 with a maturity number 7 becomes even more introspective and wisdom-focused with age. It's like the volume getting turned up on your core nature.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>

